CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, Philadelphia edition, May 11, 1940, pg. 15 reads: "A.M.E.'s Open General Conference In Detroit - No. 4 - Secretaries..Recording the mintues [minutes] of the General conference is a big job..and here are some of the men who are doing it in fine style...Left to right, Rev. D.M.Owens, of Chester, Pa.; Rev. S.E. Churchstone Lord, official stenographer; Rev. Russell S. Brown of Denver, Colo.; Rev. J.C. Beckett, Washington, D.C., all assistant secretaries. Rev. George T. Sims is secretary of the conference defeating veteran Rev. Jenkins.'
TitMainTitle: Group of ministers, from left: Reverend D. M. Owens, Reverend S. E. Churchstone Lord, Reverend Russell S. Brown, and Reverend J. C. Beckett, posed in Ebenezer AME Church during AME General Conference, Detroit
